def display_topics(model, feature_names, no_top_words):
    topic_list = []
    for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(model.components_):
        topic_terms = [feature_names[i] for i in topic.argsort()[:-no_top_words - 1:-1]]
        print("Topic %d:" % (topic_idx + 1))
        print(" ".join(topic_terms))
        topic_list.append(topic_terms)
    return topic_list

lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=num_topics, max_iter=max_iter, learning_method='online')

def get_top_words_weights(model, feature_names, topic_id, no_top_words):
    topic = model.components_[topic_id]
    top_word_indices = topic.argsort()[:-no_top_words - 1:-1]
    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_word_indices]
    top_weights = topic[top_word_indices]
    return top_words, top_weights

news_top_words, news_top_weights = get_top_words_weights(lda_model_news, newsdtm.columns, 0, 15)
reddit_top_words, reddit_top_weights = get_top_words_weights(lda_model_reddit, redditdtm.columns, 0, 15)
medium_top_words, medium_top_weights = get_top_words_weights(lda_model_medium, mediumdtm.columns, 0, 15)

news_top_weights_normalized = news_top_weights / np.sum(news_top_weights)
reddit_top_weights_normalized = reddit_top_weights / np.sum(reddit_top_weights)
medium_top_weights_normalized = medium_top_weights / np.sum(medium_top_weights)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(20, 10), sharey=True)

sns.barplot(x=news_top_weights_normalized, y=news_top_words, ax=axes[0], palette="Blues_d")
axes[0].set_title('News Topic #1', fontsize=16)
axes[0].set_xlabel('Word Importance', fontsize=12)

sns.barplot(x=reddit_top_weights_normalized, y=reddit_top_words, ax=axes[1], palette="Blues_d")
axes[1].set_title('Reddit Topic #1', fontsize=16)
axes[1].set_xlabel('Word Importance', fontsize=12)

sns.barplot(x=medium_top_weights_normalized, y=medium_top_words, ax=axes[2], palette="Blues_d")
axes[2].set_title('Medium Topic #1', fontsize=16)
axes[2].set_xlabel('Word Importance', fontsize=12)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

def plot_topic_word_table(topics, model, feature_names, no_top_words, ax, title):
    topic_words_df = pd.DataFrame()

    for i in range(len(topics)):
        words, _ = get_top_words_weights(model, feature_names, i, no_top_words)
        topic_words_df[f'Topic #{i+1}'] = words
    
    ax.axis('tight')
    ax.axis('off')
    ax.table(cellText=topic_words_df.values, colLabels=topic_words_df.columns, loc='center', cellLoc='center')
    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=16)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(20, 15), constrained_layout=True)

plot_topic_word_table(news_topics, lda_model_news, newsdtm.columns, 15, axes[0], 'News Topics')
plot_topic_word_table(reddit_topics, lda_model_reddit, redditdtm.columns, 15, axes[1], 'Reddit Topics')
plot_topic_word_table(medium_topics, lda_model_medium, mediumdtm.columns, 15, axes[2], 'Medium Topics')

plt.show()
